  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study is described in the UQ report narrative identifying wall shear stress and impeller tip clearance as potentially influential inputs, but no structured sensitivity analysis record has been linked to this package. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels under the accepted credibility argument. Decision: Accepted.",
