    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels under the MRL 5 credibility argument. Monte Carlo UQ has been performed and output uncertainty distributions are documented for all five operating points. The credibility assessment team notes that a screening sensitivity study is described verbally in the UQ report, identifying wall shear stress exposure time and impeller tip clearance as candidate dominant drivers; this narrative is considered sufficient evidence of sensitivity awareness at the current assurance level. The package is accepted as providing adequate credibility evidence for the VAD hemolysis prediction COU.",
